A '''floodway''' is a [[flood plain]] crossing for a road, built at or close to the natural ground level.<ref name="Vital Link">{{cite book |first=Leigh |last=Edmonds|author-link=Leigh Edmonds |title=The Vital Link: A History of Main Roads Western Australia 1926–1996 |publisher=University of Western Australia Press |location=Nedlands, Western Australia |year=1997 |isbn=1-875560-87-4 |page=184}}</ref>

They are designed to be submerged under water, but withstand such conditions. Typically floodways are used when the flood frequency or time span is minimal, traffic volumes are low, and the cost of a bridge is uneconomic<ref>{{cite web|author1=MRWA Waterways Section|author2=BG&E Pty Ltd|title=Floodway Design Guide|url=https://www.mainroads.wa.gov.au/Documents/Floodway%20Design%20Guide.PDF|publisher=Main Roads Western Australia|accessdate=15 April 2015|page=4|format=PDF|date=24 April 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150415031003/https://www.mainroads.wa.gov.au/Documents/Floodway%20Design%20Guide.PDF|archivedate=15 April 2015|deadurl=yes|df=dmy-all}} {{webarchive |format=addlarchives |url=https://www.webcitation.org/6XnX3UlUb?url=https://www.mainroads.wa.gov.au/Documents/Floodway%20Design%20Guide.PDF |date=15 April 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Citation | author1=[[Austroads]] | author2=Flavell, David | author3=Audora, Henry | title=Waterway design : a guide to the hydraulic design of bridges, culverts and floodways | publication-date=1994 | publisher=[[Austroads]] | isbn=978-0-85588-440-6 }}</ref> – in most cases, in rural areas.
[[File:Great Northern Highway near Payne's Find (wide).jpg|thumb|center|upright=4|Floodway on [[Great Northern Highway]], Western Australia]]
[[File:Southern Cross floodway.JPG|thumb|center|600px|Floodway and signs, eastern side of Southern Cross, Western Australia]]

